      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://core-electronics.com.au/tutorials/ws2812-addressable-leds-raspberry-pi-quickstart-guide.html">Another tutorial, uses Python code and but uses GPIO pins I expect to use.</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/GregMefford/nerves_neopixel">A NeoPixel library for Nerves. Will be using this to control the lights.</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.raspberrypi.org/forums/viewtopic.php?t=152843">It's also worthy to note that you can drive a small number of LEDs from the 5v pins.</a>
